{
  "name": "VGGT-SLAM 2.0 on TUM RGB-D (dense feed-forward SLAM)",
  "description": "VGGT-SLAM 2.0 (MIT-SPARK, RSS 2026) on a TUM RGB-D sequence, RGB-only: env_tum replays frames one per step; model_vggt_slam2__track gates them through an optical-flow keyframe filter and batches keyframes into 17-frame submaps \u2014 each submap boundary runs a VGGT forward, a SALAD loop-closure check, and a GTSAM SL(4) optimize, so track.pose updates in submap BURSTS (None until the first submap; earlier poses retro-corrected by later optimization). No depth and no intrinsics edges anywhere: VGGT self-calibrates. The loop stops when the sequence is exhausted (step_replay.terminated -> iterOut.stop); iterOut.final_stop fires finalize, which flushes the trailing partial submap (upstream's last-image trigger), and its ok gates the read-out: get_trajectory (TUM-format poses via upstream's exact writer), get_map (merged confidence-filtered colored .pcd handle), and eval_trajectory \u2014 ATE RMSE with the upstream ruler evo_ape tum -as (Sim(3) alignment is mandatory: SL(4) poses are up-to-scale), ground truth resolved from the sequence name. trajectoryViewer shows the burst-updated estimate (blue) against TUM ground truth (grey), align=on. Sequence is the placed env_tum episode; fetch with workspace/nodesets/env/env_tum/download.sh. Runs on the ac-vggt-slam server (VGGT-1B, ~16 GB VRAM budget, worker_count=1 / exclusive GPU). || Parity vs upstream main.py (2026-07-14, run 20260714_174221): fr1_xyz ATE 0.019903 BIT-EXACT vs reference 0.019903; fr1_desk 0.02531 vs 0.02469 (+0.6mm) \u2014 upstream is run-to-run deterministic (two runs both 0.024690), the desk delta is env_tum's rgb/depth/gt timestamp association dropping 17 unmatched frames (613 raw rgb -> 596 replayed, head-heavy) that upstream's raw folder glob keeps; keyframe sets diverge in the first second then lock step. C-bucket env-forced deviation, not a port defect.",
